25|$|The topics which Afrofuturistic works concern {{themselves}} include, but are {{not limited}} to: the understanding of and resistance to political systems; the importance of scientific and technological advancement to a civilization; and the redefinition of African and <b>African-American</b> <b>histories</b> (especially <b>African-American</b> claims of historical racial ties to the civilization developed in Ancient Egypt). The alienation of individuals (such as women) and non-humans (such as cyborgs) are also of particular interest.|$|R
